\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. S. marschallii} C.A. Meyer,{\i  Verz. Pfl. Cauc.} 214 (1831) (incl. {\i S. guicciardii} Boiss. & Heldr.). Plant densely caespitose; flowering-stems 15-30 cm, numerous, erect. Leaves linear-lanceolate to linear, glabrous. Inflorescence-branches with 1-3 flowers; pedicels very short. Calyx c. 12 mm, glabrous. Petals white, with linear lobes. Capsule c. 10 mm; carpophore 2-3·5 mm. {\i Mountain rocks. C. Greece} ({\b Parnassos}). Gr. ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
