\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. S. bupleuroides} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 421 (1753) ({\i S. longiflora }Ehrh.). Stems 25-80 cm, glabrous and glaucous. Basal leaves oblong-lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, long-attenuate into petiole. Inflorescence paniculate to pseudo-racemose; flowers large. Calyx 20-30 mm, glabrous and membranous-coriaceous. Petal-limb cuneate, deeply bifid, white, pinkish or greenish; coronal scales acute. Capsule 10-14 mm, included in calyx. Seeds 1·5-2 mm. {\i  S.E. & E.C. Europe.} Al Bu Cz Gr Hu Ju Rm Rs(W, K).
